article.description: — Felipe Haase had 28 points as Mercer defeated UNC Greensboro 73-64 on Sunday.
article.headline: Haase scores 28 to lift Mercer over UNC Greensboro 73-64
article.linkText: Haase scores 28 to lift Mercer over UNC Greensboro 73-64
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- — Felipe Haase had 28 points as Mercer defeated UNC Greensboro 73-64 on Sunday. Shannon Grant had 12 points for Mercer (14-13, 7-7 Southern Conference), which ended its four-game road losing streak. Kamar Robertson added 11 points. Jalen Johnson had six rebounds. Keyshaun Langley had 19 points for the Spartans (15-11, 7-7). Mohammed Abdulsalam added 11 points. Bas Leyte had seven rebounds. The Bears improve to 2-0 against the Spartans on the season. Mercer defeated UNC Greensboro 58-49 on Jan. 15. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
